                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.42/111: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-13T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 13, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Because of transportation difficulties, the Monroe Mission<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d245fn2">Educational Mission headed by Professor Paul Monroe of
                        Columbia University.</note> will be unable to proceed this spring. It plans,
                    however, to make the <pb facs="0241" n="229" xml:id="pg_229"/> trip next fall.
                    Please inform Iranian Government, emphasizing that this is merely a
                    postponement, that there is no intention of abandoning the undertaking, and
                    that, as Sadiq originally indicated, the fall is really preferable for the
                    accomplishment of the mission’s purpose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
